<br>
She inspires in me feelings of what I can only imagine to be love. I find myself thinking about her all the time, wondering what she's doing, wondering if she -- unlikely as it may be -- thinks of me too. I lose sleep over it, and what little I do get is filled with memories of the last time I saw her.<br>
<br>
So what is stopping me from putting on my manly charms?<br>
<br>
She's dating a casual friend of mine.<br>
<br>
I am filled with a gnawing agony I couldn't describe even if I knew every single word in <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Webster's</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> forward and back. Even if it <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>were</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> an option for me and her to become boyfriend / girlfriend, would I even want to? And if I still did, what kind of friend would I be? Not much of one.<br>
<br>
And everytime I glance over and see them making out or with a hand in the other's pants, I want to cry, because it's as if (to borrow from Reznor) God himself is reaching his fucking arm through just to push me down. And everyday when I go home I feel a little more dead inside than I did that morning.<br>
<br>
(Other) friends are noticing my depression, and I can only say &quot;Nothing, I'm fine&quot; so many times before it's not good enough anymore. I'm starting to write letters to her ... well, really, the same letter over and over, each draft ending up in my wastebasket shortly after my pen touches the paper ... but I doubt that's going anywhere good.<br>
<br>
I know it's emotional tripe, and I'll probably get taunted for it, but I don't really have anyone else to talk to, so ... anything you can advise would be appreciated.<br>
<br>
